<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She always looks sensational whenever she steps out.</p>

<p>And Maya Jama was sure to flaunt her sizzling curves as she enjoyed a night out with pals at Annabel's in London on Wednesday.</p>

<p>The TV and radio host, 26, looked sensational as she rocked a skin-tight white dress with a ruched detail on the sides.</p>

<p>Wow: Maya Jama looked sensational as she flaunted her sizzling curves during a night out with pals at Annabel's in London on Wednesday</p>

<p>Maya put on a leggy display in the stylish dress which boasted a high-neck line and long sleeves to emphasise her toned arms.</p>

<p>The beauty added some extra height to her frame with a pair of strappy black heels with a black and white striped pattern under her perfectly polished toes.</p>

<p>She wore her long dark locks tied into a high ponytail, letting the bottom half of her hair cascade in perfectly styled waves over her shoulders. </p>

<p>Not forgetting to accessories, Maya toted a tiny white Balenciaga handbag and added some chic hoop earrings to complete her ensemble.</p>

<p>Stunning: The radio host put on a leggy display in a tight white dress with ruched sides</p>

<p>The night out comes after Maya graced the cover of Wonderland Magazine for a sensational new shoot with an accompanying interview detailing her feelings on the industry and how she will struggle with acting </p>

<p>Maya said: 'I definitely think I'm resilient. Sometimes I surprise myself, because there's been a few times...</p>

<p>'I feel like oh my God, this is the end of the world — and then it's not the end of the world. And then I'm back.'  </p>

<p>Style: Maya tied her long dark locks  into a high ponytail, letting the bottom half of her hair cascade over her shoulders</p>

<p>Work it: She added some extra height to her frame with a pair of strappy black and white heels</p>

<p>Girls night: Maya was joined for the evening by some pals who also put on a sizzling display</p>

<p>Maya also recently revealed that she is unfazed by ex Stormzy rapping about their relationship in his songs.</p>

<p>The Vossi Bop hitmaker, 27, referred their romance in his 2019 song Lessons, but Maya insisted that it comes with the territory if you date a musician.  </p>

<p>Speaking during a Q&amp;A with singer Madison Beer as quoted by The Sun, Maya said: 'I feel that going out with an artist, you kind of sign an invisible contract where it's like, 'This is this, it's everybody's business'. </p>

<p>All in the details: Maya completed her look with a tiny Balenciaga handbag and hoop earrings</p>

<p>Here she comes: The star arrived with her pals via taxi and moved carefully as she got out of the car in her stiletto heels</p>

<p>Stunning: Maya added a full face of makeup to her ensemble, including a chic nude lipstick</p>

<p>Stormzy's song, which featured on his Heavy Is The Head album, directly name-check's Maya and their split.  </p>

<p>He raps: 'Fast forward now, my nephew's still asking for his Auntie Maya, guess this is the karma for what I done to Maya. </p>

<p>'I just stood and let it burn, I couldn't down the fire. Lord, I pray you make it easy, that's my one desire.'   </p>

<p>All over: The night out comes after Maya recently revealed that she is unfazed by ex Stormzy rapping about their relationship in his songs (pictured in February 2017)</p>
